This folder contain the files required to prepare the systems for biased simulations ( state A and state B).

1. Energy minimization: performed as for the seed crystal.

2. NVT equilibration: Temperature equilibration applied to reach target simulation conditions performed as for the seed crystal.

3. Pressure Equilibration: Pressure equilibration performed using a semi-isotropic Parrinello–Rahman barostat in three subsequent steps :

        i.  100 ps with 2 fs time step
        ii. 100 ps with 0.5 fs time step
        iii. 250 ps with 2 fs time step

    Extended simulation: System continued for 20 ns; average Lz sampled.

4. NVT production : 1000 ps with 2 fs time step

5. COM Restraint : COM restraint applied to keep the crystal centered along the simulation box.Restraint protocol performed in four steps:
    i. 1 ns with 1k restraint
    ii. 1 ns with 100k restraint
    iii. 1 ns with 1000k restraint
    iv. 25 ns with 1000k  restraint

The analysis/ folder contains three subdirectories for surface-structure CV determination, kink-site position determination, and edge-adsorption CV determination.


